effect. In the Peltier effect, the flow of electric currennt through a 
material results in a temperature difference along the material. This energy 
transfer can be described by the equation:
$\dot{Q} = \Pi I$where $\dot{Q}$ is the heat generated at a junction, $\Pi$ is the Peltier coefficient of the material, and $I$ is the current. The Peltier coefficient 
is related to the Seebeck coefficient by the equation: $ \Pi = ST$ 
