The most suitable theory for this purpose is the Landauer theory, as it is well known, simple, and equally applicable to charge and heat transport. The theory presented here is able to reproduce the results of the most successful transport theories of the last century, e.g., the Boltzmann transport equation using the relaxation time approximation. Landauer theory provides a unification of electronic and thermal transport, traditionally regarded as two completely different areas of thermoelectricity.


