\subsection{Degree of freedom in Thermoelectrics}
In thermoelectric materials, the expression of heat and charge transport is determined by a combination of microscopic variables, which are often referred to as the degrees of freedom. Among them, there are four basic degrees of freedom, i.e., lattice, charge, spin, and orbital, and they have a significant effect on the electronic structure, scattering, and the general transport nature of the material.\newline 

