\section{Material Selection}
The thermoelectric compounds based on chalcogenides have been chosen for study  due to their naturally low lattice thermal conductivity, as well as their  exceptional tunability and the prominent place they have come to hold in the  development of functional material applications. 

As such, \textbf{copper-based  chalcogenides} have attracted particular attention as an economically viable  option compared to state-of-the-art thermoelectric materials such as Bi$_2$Te$_3$,  which, being tellurium-heavy, faces considerable resource and financial  constraints. On the other hand, copper-based chalcogenides have the advantage  of copper being naturally abundant and inexpensive, in addition to having an  electron configuration that is favourable for strong phonon scattering.
