\chapter{Experimental Techniques}
\abstract{ 
This chapter follows the material-design principles from Chapter 2 and outlines the experimental techniques for producing and analyzing chalcogenide thermoelectric compounds. It begins with the synthesis route, explaining how to create phase-pure, dense pellets through controlled processing. Next, it describes the thermophysical property measurement system, including the theoretical basis and procedure for obtaining transport parameters that contribute to the \textit{zT}. Complementary methods for structural and compositional characterization are discussed: X-ray diffraction for phase identification, Raman spectroscopy for phonon mode investigation, UV-Vis-NIR spectroscopy for optical band-gap determination, and X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy for surface elemental or oxidation-state analysis. Scanning electron microscopy provides insights into the morphology and microstructure of the sintered pellets, while nano indentation offers quantitative mechanical property data. Together, these techniques form a multi-modal characterization framework for thorough analysis in the following chapters.
}
  
