\subsection{Uniaxial Hot press}
In order for TE characterization one needs a dense pellet. Dense pellets were prepared with the Uniaxial Hot Press. The ingots were ground by hand for about an hour in an agate mortar and pestle to produce a fine powder. The powder was inserted into the graphite die sets with an internal diameter of 10.3 mm, with the inner walls lined with thin sheets of graphite to prevent sticking. The die sets were inserted into the hot press chamber, which was evacuated to about$2 \times 10^{-2}$\,mbar, and maintained in dynamic vacuum throughout the process. The heating was provided by an induction coil wrapped around the die set, with the temperature monitored with a thermocouple inserted through a wilsons seal from out of the vacuum chamber. The temperature regime was established after several consolidation experiments on similar materials. the temprature profile can be seen \ref{fig:Temparature time profile}. The below is a 3-d render of the Hot-press which I have made using Blender. 
