Fourier's law of heat conduction serves as the theoretical foundation for the Laser Analysis Technique (LFA). The Fourier law of thermal conduction for a uni-dimensional heat conduction equation for an isotropic heat conducting for sample can be defined as: 
\begin{equation}
    {\frac{\partial^{2}T}{\partial x^{2}}}={\frac{1}{\alpha}}~{\frac{\partial T}{\partial t}}
    \label{fourier-equation-heat}
\end{equation}
Where, The temperature distribution of the sample is described by the one-dimensional heat conduction equation for an isotropic heat-conducting material. T stands for temperature, and x for sample thickness (y-axis) in this equation. ~\cite{sudhansundar}

