\section{Nanoindentation}
Nano-Indentation, taking its derivative form from its name, has been a Neo-convenctional non-destructive approach in order to measure various mechanical properties of materials, especially where traditional approaches (macro \& micro-indentation) use Mohs-9 materials like Diamond to place an indent onto a sample and with a user-specific load, which will be held for brief amount of time and shall be removed, and the resulting indentation shall be measured using Light microscopy. And the Hardness can be defined as: 
\begin{equation}
    H = \frac{P_{max}} {A_r} 
\end{equation}
where A$_r$ is the residual indentation area, P$_{max}$ is the maximum user-applied load, and H is Hardness. Such techniques have a wide range of difficulties; for example, they may have poor resolution.  
