from an polynomial approximation available here: \cite{nanoindent-wiki}, One can conclude the modulus as: 
$$\frac{1}{E_r} = \frac{1 - \nu^2}{E} + \frac{1 - \nu_i^2}{E_i},$$
in which $\nu$ and $E$ are the ratio of Poisson and modulus of elasticity of the semiconductor sample respectively and $\nu_i$ and $E_i$ the numbers of the indenter tip.

