\section{Raman Spectroscopy}
Scattering is a fundamental light-matter interaction that has attracted interest since its discovery. 
If a light shines onto a particle with a frequency $\nu_{in}$ and the scattered light has $\nu_{out}$, $\nu_{out}$ =  $\nu_{in}$, then it is considered as Elastic-Rayleigh Scattering. 
There can be another Scenario where $\nu_{out} \neq \nu_{out}$; then it is Raman Scattering. This is caused by the coupling of light between the sample's rotational-vibrational states and those of the source. 
