 \section{Scanning Electron Microscopy}
Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) has been the goto for understanding material in depth in the recnt times topographies. SEM provides high-resolution images of the granular structure of materials by utilizing a tight focussed electron beam and measuring secondary emitted electrons that come off the surface of the specimen. These images allow a scrupulous examination of grain boundaries arrangement, which play a significant role in the analysis of material behaviour and property. In this thesis, the SEM images have been exploited to evaluate the importance of the grain boundaries to the physical transport characteristics.
