measured Seebeck coefficient, electrical conductivity, and thermal conductivity. It is worth noting that the reference $zT$ of pristine CuSbSe$_2$ has been reported 
to be as low as $\sim$0.1~\cite{D1}; in the present series, $zT$ reaches 
approximately 0.3 at 630~K, despite the coexistence of secondary impurity phases.

